Mobile Architecture

The goal is to build a mobile version of the SymFlow platform that is:

Primary: Click-based UI
I propose a click-based interaction model as the primary interface.
Why?
Most logistics users (drivers, operators) need:
Quick actions
Minimal thinking
Faster than typing or speaking

Example:
Upload POD → single button
Track shipment → one tap

Secondary: AI/Natural Language (Optional)
Add a lightweight AI assistant for advanced queries
Examples:
“Show delayed shipments”
“Check delivery status for order 123”
This improves UX but should NOT replace main UI

Tech Stack Decision
Chosen: React Native
Why React Native?
Cross-platform (Android + iOS)
Faster development
Reusable logic from React web app
Large ecosystem
Why not Native (Kotlin/Swift)?
Higher development time
Separate codebases
Not ideal for a small team/startup


4. Architecture Design

Mobile App (React Native)
        ↓
API Layer (Django/DRF)
        ↓
Backend Services
        ↓
Database (PostgreSQL)
        ↓
External Services (S3, AI APIs)

Key Features & Design Choices
1. Authentication
JWT-based authentication
Secure API communication
2. API Communication
REST APIs using Django backend
Use Axios / Fetch
3. State Management
Redux / Context API
Helps manage:
User data
Orders
App state
4. Offline Support (Important for logistics)

Since drivers may have poor network:

Cache important data locally
Sync when network is available
5. Performance Optimization
Lazy loading screens
Image compression before upload (for POD)
Background sync

